!! What it does

Explide turns config tiddlers into isolated `$testcase` sandboxes. You define which plugins and shadow tiddlers to include, override fields with the `$rri$:` prefix remapping, add ad-hoc tiddlers, and see the assembled result live — all without leaving the wiki.

!! Features

* ''Config-driven pipeline'' — each tiddler with `rri.type: explide/config` becomes a full IDE
* ''Plugin import'' — import entire plugins or cherry-pick individual shadow tiddlers
* ''Bulk import'' — import multiple tiddlers at once using a filter expression
* ''`$rri$:` field remapping'' — override any field on explide data tiddlers without colliding with real fields
* ''Field editor'' — FIELDS tab for adding, editing, and deleting `$rri$:` remapped fields
* ''Ad-hoc tiddlers'' — create simple text-only tiddlers inline for quick prototyping
* ''Snapshot & diff'' — take snapshots of explide data, compare changes, and restore previous states
* ''Diagnostics'' — detect missing plugins, missing tiddlers, unused imports, and stale snapshots
* ''Layout toggle'' — switch between stacked and side-by-side (config + preview) layout
* ''Output tiddler'' — configurable testcase output (defaults to `Output`)
* ''ViewTemplate integration'' — the IDE renders automatically when viewing a config tiddler

!! Quick start

# Create a new tiddler and set `rri.type` to `explide/config`
# Open the CONFIG tab and import a plugin (e.g., `$:/plugins/rimir/components`)
# Click the {{$:/core/images/new-button}} button next to a shadow tiddler to add it as explide data
# Switch to the explide data tab to edit the overridden tiddler in the EDITOR
# Create an ad-hoc tiddler named `Output` — this is what the testcase Output tab renders
# Use DIFF to compare your changes against the original shadow tiddler or a snapshot

<$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template/templates/callout" type="info">
<$fill $name="body">Explide is pure wikitext — no JS modules, no server restart needed. All changes take effect immediately.</$fill>
</$transclude>

